"### Split age in two categories
This is an example score calculation that shows how to dichotomize a measure. In this case we split the age variable in month into two categories $\mbox{age}<120$ and $\mbox{age}\geq120$.
```
var promises = use(["age"]);
```
This function will return the value 1 or 0 dependent on the value of the argument.
```
function calcDichot(age) {
    if (age > 120)
        return 1;
    return 0;
}
```

Here we first wait for the server to fulfill the promise of getting access to the age variable. Then we will get a copy of the data and run our calcDichot funtion on each age value saving the results into the new age_dichot variable.
```
Promise.all(promises).then( function() {
  var data = new DataFrame(allMeasures);
  data = data.map(row => row.set('age_dichot', calcDichot(row.get('age'))));
  update(data, 'age_dichot');
});
```
We can verify the success of the computation in the table and histogram displayed."
